Title: Spontaneous Polarization of the $\Bbb Z _{n}$-Baxter Model
Authors: Yas-Hiro Quano
Comments: 14p, RIMS-930
Journal-ref: Mod. Phys. Lett. A8 (1993) 3363-3376
\\
  We show that correlation functions of the $\bz _n $-Baxter model in the
principal regime satisfy a system of difference equations. We obtain the
spontaneous polarization of the $\bz _n $-Baxter model as a solution of the
simplest difference equation.
